And I'm just going to go over this real quickly. So it's Shiny for R, Python compiled to WebAssembly

00:07:49.040 --> 00:07:54.480
running in the browser. So the traditional model for a Shiny app deployment is you have R or Python

00:07:54.480 --> 00:08:01.040
running on a server, and then the client computers connect to the server, but most of the code is

00:08:01.040 --> 00:08:05.920
running on the server there. With a Shiny Live deployment, the server is dumb, and it just sends

00:08:05.920 --> 00:08:13.920
out some files, and then you have R or Python running in the browser. So that has some implications

00:08:13.920 --> 00:08:19.279
for security. So when R and Python is running in the browser, it's in the browser security sandbox,

00:08:19.279 --> 00:08:24.160
which is very safe. You know, it's been battle-tested on billions of, literally billions

00:08:24.160 --> 00:08:29.279
of devices over the years. It can't access local files on your computer and has restricted network

00:08:29.279 --> 00:08:33.200
connectivity. So it makes it pretty safe to run all the code that the LLM generates.

00:08:34.159 --> 00:08:38.159
